body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Solutions. My name is Harold Jones. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Shirley. Can you provide your phone number so we can reach out to you if needed?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is six five zero- five five five- eight eight eight eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Shirley. And could you also provide your email address for correspondence?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is s.harris@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information, Shirley. Is there anything specific you'd like to discuss with us today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, I am feeling disappointed about the data management at the dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your concern, Shirley. We will look into that for you. Thank you for bringing that to our attention.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Shirley. We will work on resolving the issue. Have a great day.
